it with `--auto medium/high`)\\n- **No session state created** until SaveStep's late fallback (after agent is done)\\n- **No PrePromptState** — pre-untracked file baseline is lost\\n\\n## Approach: Install `user-prompt-submit` on Droid's SessionStart event type\\n\\nThe fix is entirely within Droid's hook installation code. When installing hooks, register the `user-prompt-submit` command as a **second hook under the `SessionStart` event type** in `.factory/settings.json`. This way, when Droid fires its SessionStart event, both commands run:\\n\\n1. `entire hooks factoryai-droid session-start` → SessionStart event → banner, concurrent session check\\n2. `entire hooks factoryai-droid user-prompt-submit` → TurnStart event → session initialized, ACTIVE phase\\n\\n**Why this works:**\\n- `userPromptSubmitRaw` is a superset of `sessionInfoRaw` (same fields + `prompt`). When SessionStart sends `{session_id, transcript_path}`, `json.Unmarshal` succeeds — `Prompt` is just `\\\"\\\"`.\\n- If `UserPromptSubmit` fires later (interactive/stream-jsonrpc mode), it's a benign ACTIVE→ACTIVE transition\\n- If it doesn't fire (exec mode), the session is already ACTIVE from SessionStart\\n- `removeEntireHooks` matches by `\\\"entire \\\"` prefix — both commands are properly removed during uninstall\\n\\n**Resulting `.factory/settings.json` SessionStart entry:**\\n```json\\n\\\"SessionStart\\\": [{\\n  \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": [\\n    {\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks factoryai-droid session-start\\\"},\\n    {\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks factoryai-droid user-prompt-submit\\\"}\\n  ]\\n}]\\n```\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks.go` — InstallHooks\\n\\nAfter the existing `sessionStart` hook installation (line ~158), add `userPromptSubmitCmd` to the `sessionStart` hook type:\\n\\n```go\\n// Also install user-prompt-submit on SessionStart to ensure TurnStart fires\\n// even when UserPromptSubmit doesn't (e.g., droid exec mode).\\n// The user-prompt-submit handler gracefully handles SessionStart's stdin format\\n// (userPromptSubmitRaw is a superset of sessionInfoRaw; Prompt defaults to \\\"\\\").\\nif !hookCommandExists(sessionStart, userPromptSubmitCmd) {\\n    sessionStart = addHookToMatcher(sessionStart, \\\"\\\", userPromptSubmitCmd)\\n    count++\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNo other code changes needed:\\n- **UninstallHooks** — `removeEntireHooks` already removes all `\\\"entire ...\\\"` commands from all hook types\\n- **AreHooksInstalled** — Already checks for `\\\"entire hooks factoryai-droid stop\\\"` which is sufficient\\n- **GetHookNames/GetSupportedHooks** — No changes; `user-prompt-submit` already exists as a subcommand\\n- **ParseHookEvent** — No changes; `parseTurnStart` already handles missing `prompt` field\\n\\n### 2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks_test.go` — Update tests\\n\\n- Update `TestInstallHooks` to verify SessionStart has TWO commands (session-start + user-prompt-submit)\\n- Add test: verify `parseTurnStart` handles SessionStart-format stdin (missing `prompt` field)\\n- Update uninstall tests to verify both commands are removed from SessionStart\\n\\n### Files Summary\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks.go` | Add `userPromptSubmitCmd` to `sessionStart` in InstallHooks (~3 lines) |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks_test.go` | Update install/uninstall tests |\\n\\n**No changes to:** `event.go`, `lifecycle.go`, `phase.go`, or any other agent's code.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint` — passes\\n2. `mise run test` — unit tests pass\\n3. `mise run test:integration` — integration tests pass\\n4. Manual: `entire enable --agent factoryai-droid` then inspect `.factory/settings.json` — verify SessionStart has both commands\\n5. Manual: `entire disable --agent factoryai-droid` then inspect — verify both commands removed\